 :tx/rationale "RFL TASK AUDIT — 5 issues found:\n\nISSUE 1: Missing :action/timestamp and :action/features schema attributes in RFL-1. The timestamp is needed for latency computation (RFL-3). The features vector (6 R(t) metric values) is needed for the learning algorithm (RFL-4). Without features, RFL-4 can't build the X matrix for regression. Solution: add :action/timestamp (Long, unix millis) and :action/features (String, JSON array of 6 floats) to the schema.\n\nISSUE 2: RFL-2 should be CENTRALIZED in main.rs, not scattered across command files. Recording the projected action in every command builder (status.rs, task.rs, etc.) creates N duplication points. Better: record ONCE in main.rs after run() returns, by checking if output.json contains _acp field. The exit_warn_path is already extracted before run() consumes the command.\n\nISSUE 3: RFL-4's normal equations (X^T X)^{-1} X^T y may fail when X^T X is singular (collinear features — pagerank and betweenness often correlate). Fix: ridge regression w = (X^T X + lambda*I)^{-1} X^T y where lambda=0.01. One line change that prevents all singularity crashes.\n\nISSUE 4: The 50-datapoint threshold means no learning for 2-3 sessions. Add a 'preview mode' to RFL-5 dashboard: show hypothetical learned weights even below threshold, with disclaimer. This gives immediate feedback that the system is LEARNING, even before it activates.\n\nISSUE 5: TEST-RFL-E2E missing cold-start test (first command in session has no previous recommendation) and regularization test (collinear features don't crash)."
